WEBVTT

00:11.440 --> 00:13.960
Previously on
"Queens of Mystery"...

00:13.960 --> 00:16.760
Volcanic Youth are recording
a reunion record.

00:16.760 --> 00:19.400
Well, hello, you lovely people.

00:19.400 --> 00:21.040
-Bloody cow!
-ELECTRA: Get off me!

00:21.040 --> 00:23.160
-Girls! Stop!
-Kurt, is that you?

00:24.280 --> 00:26.120
Electra Bliss is dead.

00:27.440 --> 00:28.880
She was being watched.

00:28.880 --> 00:30.480
KURT: There was a reel
on there yesterday.

00:30.480 --> 00:31.640
The tape's been taken.

00:31.640 --> 00:33.520
You can't suppress the truth!

00:33.520 --> 00:34.640
Truth? [ Laughs ]

00:34.640 --> 00:36.280
It's over, man.

00:36.280 --> 00:38.440
How can you claim
to run a record company

00:38.440 --> 00:40.000
if you don't answer
your damn phone?

00:41.400 --> 00:43.800
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

01:12.600 --> 01:13.760
[ Caws ]

01:43.400 --> 01:45.480
NARRATOR:
To lose one lead singer

01:45.480 --> 01:48.040
may be regarded
as a misfortune.

01:48.040 --> 01:53.680
To lose bothand your manager
looks like carelessness.

01:54.480 --> 01:55.880
To Inspector Thorne,

01:55.880 --> 01:59.040
that meant tough decisions
needed to be made.

01:59.040 --> 02:01.480
There's a murderer out here.

02:01.480 --> 02:03.240
Nobody leaves
until they're in custody.

02:03.240 --> 02:05.400
But what if someone else
is killed, sir?

02:05.400 --> 02:08.160
We'd better get it solved before
that can happen, Sergeant.

02:08.759 --> 02:11.160
Or we'll both have blood
on our hands.

02:17.800 --> 02:19.520
MATILDA: [ Sighs ]

02:21.760 --> 02:23.040
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

02:26.920 --> 02:31.120
To twist the knife isn't just
an expression in this case.

02:31.120 --> 02:32.560
What, you think the killer
wanted it to hurt,

02:32.560 --> 02:34.720
-like a punishment?
-Maybe.

02:35.760 --> 02:38.120
Then, again, perhaps they knew
it would do more damage quickly.

02:38.120 --> 02:40.400
The body also looks like
it's been moved.

02:40.400 --> 02:42.240
Because of an interruption?

02:42.240 --> 02:43.920
Well, it'd stop it
being found as fast.

02:43.920 --> 02:45.960
Either could be true.

02:47.720 --> 02:50.320
[ Soft music plays ]

02:53.040 --> 02:56.960
In that perfect moment,
Matilda couldn't help thinking

02:56.960 --> 03:01.840
what a great team
she and Dr. Daniel Lynch made.

03:01.840 --> 03:04.120
Uh, he --
Uh, it's a kitchen knife.

03:04.120 --> 03:07.040
-Mm.
-Seems to be a good-quality one.

03:07.040 --> 03:09.040
Probably German.

03:09.040 --> 03:11.760
And his knowledge
of well-engineered cutlery

03:11.760 --> 03:14.200
did nothing to dampen
her ardor.

03:14.200 --> 03:16.040
I also got the lab results back

03:16.040 --> 03:18.040
-from Electra Bliss' autopsy.
-Mm.

03:18.040 --> 03:19.560
There was cocaine in her system.

03:20.200 --> 03:21.920
That explains why the table
was wiped down.

03:21.920 --> 03:23.200
Someone cleaned up the room.

03:23.200 --> 03:25.720
To protect her reputation
or themselves?

03:25.720 --> 03:28.560
She was a rock star. They were
covering their own tracks.

03:32.840 --> 03:35.040
-Matilda?
-Terry.

03:35.040 --> 03:36.080
-[ Breathes deeply ]
-Right.

03:39.520 --> 03:43.160
There's only two shops in London
that stock Gray River Vodka.

03:43.160 --> 03:45.200
Here's
their client delivery list.

03:46.760 --> 03:48.600
They have Collins.

03:48.600 --> 03:50.320
Good work.

03:50.320 --> 03:52.240
She was in the vicinity
of both crimes

03:52.240 --> 03:54.720
and had motive
to kill Electra Bliss.

03:54.720 --> 03:56.600
Plus, we've identified
the drill bit used.

03:56.600 --> 03:59.520
It's a standard high-speed
with a 1/4-inch shank.

03:59.520 --> 04:00.880
They're very common.

04:00.880 --> 04:02.880
I've been thinking
about that peephole.

04:02.880 --> 04:04.640
It's almost too small.

04:11.880 --> 04:16.279
As the newly widowed Tallulah
signaled her grief with tears,

04:16.279 --> 04:19.320
those around her were left
to wonder if they were,

04:19.320 --> 04:23.000
in fact,
of the crocodilian variety.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.960
Enough with the filming already!

04:24.960 --> 04:27.560
I'm protecting us.

04:27.560 --> 04:30.560
No one's gonna try
and murder anyone on camera.

04:30.560 --> 04:33.120
Get that thing out of my face!

04:35.600 --> 04:37.320
-[ Feedback squeals ]
-Ow! Oh!

04:37.320 --> 04:39.680
Hey, man.
That was unnecessary.

04:42.440 --> 04:43.640
[ Tallulah sobs ]

04:43.640 --> 04:45.600
Switch it off, please,
Mr. Wimmer.

04:49.600 --> 04:51.000
Viv, I need a word with you.

04:51.000 --> 04:52.720
In private.

04:52.720 --> 04:54.200
Follow me, please.

05:09.640 --> 05:11.600
So...

05:12.200 --> 05:14.320
...are you a cocaine user,
Ms. Collins?

05:14.320 --> 05:17.040
No. Stuff makes me
climb up the walls.

05:17.040 --> 05:19.040
Gray River Vodka
more your thing?

05:20.320 --> 05:24.000
I found a bottle by the road
where Ringo the dog was killed.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.040
Ringo?
Is that his name?

05:26.040 --> 05:27.840
That's a bummer.

05:28.760 --> 05:30.280
It wasn't me.

05:30.280 --> 05:33.880
I told you --
I'm -- I'm off the booze now.

05:33.880 --> 05:36.400
A local stocker said
you're a very loyal customer.

05:36.400 --> 05:39.480
Ah, well, see, sometimes,
I buy gifts for people.

05:39.480 --> 05:42.240
Why deny knowing Electra Bliss
wanted you out of the band?

05:43.320 --> 05:45.080
We have the note
that she wrote to you.

05:46.480 --> 05:49.200
[ Sighs ]
Well [Clears throat]

05:49.200 --> 05:51.640
the thing is,
you see, I'm, um...

05:51.640 --> 05:53.360
I'm paranoid.

05:53.360 --> 05:56.280
My psychiatrist thinks
that it's because

05:56.280 --> 05:58.080
of all the hard living
in my past,

05:58.080 --> 06:01.920
and, um -- And so really
what happened was, you know,

06:01.920 --> 06:04.320
I-I just panicked.

06:04.320 --> 06:07.320
-How come?
-Well, she wanted me out,

06:07.320 --> 06:09.400
and then she was killed,
and so it --

06:09.400 --> 06:12.200
And it's gonna look like
that I'm guilty,

06:12.200 --> 06:14.640
which, you know, I'm not.

06:16.800 --> 06:19.800
You were seen coming out of
the studio at 2:20 on the night

06:19.800 --> 06:21.480
Electra Bliss was killed.

06:23.320 --> 06:25.240
She slipped the note
under my door,

06:25.240 --> 06:28.320
and I don't sleep much at night,
so I read it,

06:28.320 --> 06:31.560
and then I watched her,
you know, go outside.

06:31.560 --> 06:33.440
-And you followed her out there?
-Yes.

06:33.440 --> 06:36.240
Because I wanted to tell her
she can't fire me.

06:36.240 --> 06:39.440
Being in this band,
it's my life.

06:41.480 --> 06:43.920
ELECTRA: Volcanic Youth
wouldn't exist without me.

06:45.640 --> 06:48.000
Now, you, on the other hand...

06:52.840 --> 06:55.000
[ Clears throat ]

06:55.000 --> 06:56.360
"I won't let your inability

06:56.360 --> 06:58.800
to deal with the past
ruin our future."

07:03.240 --> 07:05.120
What in your past
is she referring to?

07:07.320 --> 07:08.840
Uh, well, I had
a rough childhood,

07:08.840 --> 07:10.480
you see, and that's why I drink.

07:10.480 --> 07:13.040
Well, I don'tdrink.
I used to drink. I don't drink.

07:16.560 --> 07:19.720
We found you last night
standing over Len's body.

07:22.720 --> 07:26.320
I told you.
I was stir-crazy.

07:26.320 --> 07:29.280
I just needed a walk,
and then there he was.

07:29.280 --> 07:30.920
A walk in the cold
and the dark?

07:30.920 --> 07:35.280
Look, I've got a lot going on at
the moment in my mind, you know?

07:35.280 --> 07:37.080
I mean, Susan's death,

07:37.080 --> 07:40.800
and then Len trying
to rush-release her last song.

07:40.800 --> 07:43.320
I mean, this is
really heavy stuff, you know?

07:43.320 --> 07:45.280
Her last song?
When did she record it?

07:46.000 --> 07:47.840
Well, on the night she died.

07:47.840 --> 07:49.120
And Len had the tape?

07:51.000 --> 07:52.400
Yes.

07:52.400 --> 07:54.800
He said that he slipped back
into the studio

07:54.800 --> 07:56.640
first thing
the following morning

07:56.640 --> 07:59.200
and before they sealed
the place off.

08:00.760 --> 08:03.600
Look, are you gonna charge me?
Because my psychiatrist

08:03.600 --> 08:05.800
says that I don't deal very well
with stress,

08:05.800 --> 08:08.320
and, you know, I think
I've answered enough of --

08:08.320 --> 08:10.680
of all your questions now
and all that.

08:10.680 --> 08:12.600
-[ Thud ]
-Ooh!

08:14.280 --> 08:15.880
[ Clears throat ]

08:16.600 --> 08:18.080
We came in that way.

08:20.160 --> 08:22.320
You're right.
I remember.

08:22.320 --> 08:24.160
[ Door opens ]

08:25.920 --> 08:27.920
[ Breathes shakily ]

08:30.160 --> 08:33.320
JANE: What were you doing
in a bin anyway?

08:33.320 --> 08:36.240
So, the bassist, Gina,
was threatening Len,

08:36.240 --> 08:38.039
wanting money for something?

08:38.039 --> 08:39.880
We should tell Matilda.

08:39.880 --> 08:41.360
BETH: You think that's motive
for murder?

08:41.360 --> 08:43.320
I don't know.

08:43.320 --> 08:45.560
The body looked staged to me,
like, uh...

08:45.560 --> 08:46.960
like he'd been stabbed

08:46.960 --> 08:49.360
and then positioned
under the statue of Apollo.

08:49.360 --> 08:52.160
God of music, song, and poetry.

08:52.160 --> 08:55.040
CAT: Huh. The three things that
Len didn't give a fig about.

08:55.040 --> 08:56.960
Oh, he loved the music-biz
parties and the girls,

08:56.960 --> 09:00.400
but the one thing that
he really cared about was cash.

09:00.400 --> 09:03.840
Maybe the killer knew that
and was making a statement.

09:03.840 --> 09:07.240
Like some kind
of poetic justice?

09:07.240 --> 09:08.680
BETH: Mm.

09:13.840 --> 09:15.800
-How big's this tape?
-It's about that big.

09:15.800 --> 09:17.360
It'll be in a box.

09:28.760 --> 09:30.040
"Retrodisc Records."

09:30.040 --> 09:32.120
Volcanic Youth's new contract.

09:38.800 --> 09:41.640
Steven W. Tyne.

09:41.640 --> 09:44.320
Let's get in contact
with Mr. Tyne.

09:44.320 --> 09:46.800
What's in the other one, Terry?

09:46.800 --> 09:50.760
He tried not to smile
at her use of his first name,

09:50.760 --> 09:52.320
but it was hard.

09:52.320 --> 09:54.400
TERRY: It's a legal letter,
banning Jonas Wimmer

09:54.400 --> 09:57.120
from ever using
an interview he did with Len.

09:57.120 --> 09:59.960
Now, that's some TV
I want to see.

10:19.480 --> 10:21.080
Ready?

10:22.720 --> 10:26.720
ELECTRA: ♪ Oh, the reason ♪

10:26.720 --> 10:30.080
♪ For my floods of tears♪

10:30.080 --> 10:33.200
♪ Is 'cause you're saying
we're♪

10:33.200 --> 10:38.320
♪ Surely dying♪

10:38.320 --> 10:41.600
♪ Remember me♪

10:41.600 --> 10:45.440
♪ 'Cause that's all you've got♪

10:45.440 --> 10:49.080
♪ 'Cause I'm a road♪

10:49.080 --> 10:52.320
♪ That don't go home♪

10:54.680 --> 10:55.920
Kurt?

10:56.840 --> 10:58.880
Kurt, stop messing about.

10:59.560 --> 11:01.760
-Kurt, is that you?
-It's not me.

11:01.760 --> 11:03.160
I'm -- I'm not in there.

11:05.280 --> 11:06.920
Kurt, this isn't funny anymore.

11:06.920 --> 11:08.440
[ Clatter]

11:09.400 --> 11:10.720
[ Speaks indistinctly]

11:10.720 --> 11:11.920
What did she say
right at the end?

11:11.920 --> 11:13.200
TERRY:
I couldn't make it out.

11:13.200 --> 11:14.280
[ Tape rewinding ]

11:14.280 --> 11:16.560
I think it was...

11:16.560 --> 11:17.680
Sorry.

11:17.680 --> 11:19.600
..."sorry."

11:25.880 --> 11:27.360
It says here Apollo

11:27.360 --> 11:30.160
was also the god
of protection of the young.

11:30.160 --> 11:34.400
Who Len Savage literally spent
most of his life exploiting.

11:34.400 --> 11:36.520
And the sun, light, prophecy.

11:36.520 --> 11:39.080
Not to mention archery,
the plague,

11:39.080 --> 11:41.120
medicine, and knowledge.

11:41.120 --> 11:43.040
-Busy chap.
-[ Clicks tongue ]

11:43.760 --> 11:47.560
So, um...maybe we're barking up
the wrong tree or statue

11:47.560 --> 11:51.520
or whatever with
this whole poetic-justice thing.

11:51.520 --> 11:53.480
Okay.

11:55.320 --> 11:58.200
-What about water?
-What about it?

11:58.200 --> 12:03.120
Well, Len's body
was dumped in water.

12:03.120 --> 12:05.080
Was Apollo the god of that, too?

12:05.080 --> 12:06.320
No.
That was Poseidon.

12:07.800 --> 12:08.880
[ Knock on door ]

12:12.600 --> 12:13.840
Put that down, please.

12:13.840 --> 12:15.680
Sorry.
Force of habit.

12:15.680 --> 12:17.640
I forget
I'm holding it sometimes.

12:17.640 --> 12:20.280
The interview you did that
Len didn't want you using --

12:20.280 --> 12:22.040
I need to see it.

12:23.120 --> 12:24.360
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

12:24.360 --> 12:26.280
[ Reporters
shouting indistinctly ]

12:27.200 --> 12:29.440
-Are you sure about this?
-Mm-hmm.

12:29.440 --> 12:31.440
Len's gone.

12:31.440 --> 12:33.000
Let's do this.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.040
[ Shouting continues ]

12:36.040 --> 12:38.080
REPORTER: Who's gonna be
the third member of the band?

12:38.080 --> 12:40.920
[ Voice breaking ] We have
a short statement to make.

12:42.280 --> 12:44.640
The death of Electra Bliss

12:44.640 --> 12:47.360
and now the band's
long-term manager, Len Savage...

12:47.360 --> 12:50.000
-[ Blows nose ]
-...is a huge tragedy.

12:50.000 --> 12:52.640
But after careful consideration,

12:52.640 --> 12:56.520
we've decided that
Volcanic Youth must continue

12:56.520 --> 12:59.560
and that the two of us will
soon be recording her last song

12:59.560 --> 13:01.680
and then going out on tour.

13:01.680 --> 13:03.800
Thank you for your support
during this difficult time.

13:03.800 --> 13:05.360
[ Reporters
shouting indistinctly ]

13:05.360 --> 13:07.560
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

13:09.880 --> 13:11.600
JONAS:
I heard that Volcanic Youth

13:11.600 --> 13:14.960
nearly split up
after the '85 tour.

13:14.960 --> 13:18.320
Yeah, well, you know, when
your lead singer dies, it's --

13:18.320 --> 13:19.840
The surviving members
of the band

13:19.840 --> 13:22.960
are bound to consider
their futures, you know?

13:22.960 --> 13:25.560
JONAS: Yeah, but you know there
are all other sorts of rumors

13:25.560 --> 13:27.960
flying around
that Nikki was murdered

13:27.960 --> 13:30.880
or that she didn't want to be
famous and faked her own death.

13:30.880 --> 13:33.320
You know what?
I've changed my mind.

13:33.320 --> 13:34.680
I don't want to be
in your crappy film.

13:34.680 --> 13:35.520
JONAS: Oh, wait. Look...

13:35.520 --> 13:37.160
Enough!

13:39.760 --> 13:41.680
You seem to have hit a nerve.

13:41.680 --> 13:43.840
You're not wrong.

13:44.760 --> 13:48.240
He made it a condition for me
being allowed to film the band

13:48.240 --> 13:50.320
during the making of this album
that I sign a letter

13:50.320 --> 13:53.240
to never sell
or even use this clip.

13:53.240 --> 13:55.280
Your documentary just keeps
getting more interesting,

13:55.280 --> 13:56.600
doesn't it?

13:56.600 --> 13:58.840
First Electra Bliss,
then Len Savage.

13:58.840 --> 14:01.840
[ Laughing ] I know.
It's practically making itself.

14:04.720 --> 14:09.800
But...obviously, I wish [Coughs]
none of this had happened.

14:09.800 --> 14:11.200
It's all very tragic.

14:12.040 --> 14:14.760
[ Cellphone rings ]

14:14.760 --> 14:16.880
-[ Cellphone beeps ]
-What is it, Cat?

14:16.880 --> 14:20.320
I thought you should know.
I overhead Gina arguing with Len

14:20.320 --> 14:21.760
about money that she was owed.

14:21.760 --> 14:23.320
Okay. Thanks. I have to go.
I'll call you back. Bye.

14:24.800 --> 14:28.000
Where were you yesterday between
6:00 and 7:00, Mr. Wimmer?

14:28.000 --> 14:30.960
In here, editing the rushes.

14:30.960 --> 14:32.840
Mattie's interviewing a suspect,

14:32.840 --> 14:35.120
-and she's forgotten to hang up.
-Put it on speaker, then.

14:35.120 --> 14:37.000
MATILDA: Couldn't have written
a better plot, could you?

14:37.000 --> 14:38.240
The band going to the house

14:38.240 --> 14:40.400
of a world-famous
reclusive rock star,

14:40.400 --> 14:43.200
and then the lead singer
and their manager get murdered.

14:43.200 --> 14:45.400
She makes a good point.

14:45.400 --> 14:47.520
Got everything
a decent detective novel needs.

14:47.520 --> 14:51.200
Interesting characters,
quirky world, plenty of mystery.

14:51.200 --> 14:53.080
-Even some tunes.
-MATILDA: I'd imagine you'd have

14:53.080 --> 14:55.280
film companies
lining up to buy it.

14:55.280 --> 14:58.120
A great documentary maker
is a lucky documentary maker.

14:58.120 --> 15:00.160
And that's you, is it,
Mr. Wimmer?

15:00.160 --> 15:01.680
You were just lucky?

15:02.800 --> 15:04.840
[ Man yodeling ]

15:04.840 --> 15:07.640
NARRATOR: Jonas was, in fact,
the latest in a long line

15:07.640 --> 15:10.640
of highly unfortunate Wimmers.

15:10.640 --> 15:12.240
His great-grandfather
had been killed

15:12.240 --> 15:15.000
in a freak yodeling accident.

15:15.000 --> 15:18.440
His grandfather lost to
a donkey in local elections

15:18.440 --> 15:20.560
and never fully recovered.

15:20.560 --> 15:22.040
And his father...

15:23.040 --> 15:24.840
Well, the less said
about his encounter

15:24.840 --> 15:28.440
with a Samoan arm-wrestling
champion, the better.

15:28.440 --> 15:30.600
So these murders
were either a sign

15:30.600 --> 15:34.120
that the Wimmer luck
was finally changing

15:34.120 --> 15:39.240
or that Jonas had decided to
change that luck for himself.

15:39.240 --> 15:41.760
-May I?
-What are you...

15:48.280 --> 15:50.480
MATILDA:
Had you worked with Len before?

15:50.480 --> 15:51.920
No.

15:54.200 --> 15:55.680
This is my first film.

15:55.680 --> 15:57.120
MATILDA:
So, why did he hire you?

15:57.120 --> 15:58.760
Len didn't.

15:59.560 --> 16:02.200
Fairsight Films hired me
after I answered their ad

16:02.200 --> 16:05.200
for a documentary maker
in Wall of Rockmagazine.

16:06.200 --> 16:07.640
-[ Cellphone beeps ]
-Check it out.

16:10.440 --> 16:12.120
[ Keyboard clacking ]

16:17.000 --> 16:19.760
No website for Fairsight Films.

16:19.760 --> 16:22.120
Where can we get back copies
of Wall of Rockmagazine?

16:22.120 --> 16:23.720
Well, Pat Cardosa
has an Aladdin's cave

16:23.720 --> 16:25.080
of music-related stuff --

16:25.080 --> 16:28.520
mags, albums, films, the works.

16:29.880 --> 16:31.600
JANE: There is a link
to this site, though.

16:43.920 --> 16:46.720
-I've got to go.
-Cat?

16:46.720 --> 16:48.800
[ Bell dinging ]

17:02.440 --> 17:05.000
MATILDA: How big is the business
end of that microphone?

17:05.000 --> 17:07.599
About 1/4 inch?

17:07.599 --> 17:09.480
Your guess is as good as mine.

17:09.480 --> 17:12.960
-What, you don't know?
-It's not my mic.

17:13.880 --> 17:16.440
I borrowed it off Kurt after
Sir Ray broke mine this morning.

17:23.800 --> 17:25.440
Mr. Lee.

17:29.200 --> 17:31.560
ELECTRA: [ Laughing]

17:31.560 --> 17:33.280
[ Sighs]

17:34.240 --> 17:35.920
[ Laughs]

17:37.480 --> 17:38.640
Oops!

17:38.640 --> 17:40.280
Oh.

17:41.120 --> 17:43.000
I love the sound of her.

17:43.000 --> 17:44.720
-That's all.
-[ Laughs]

17:44.720 --> 17:47.240
She was so full of life.

17:47.240 --> 17:49.480
MATILDA: Were you listening
the night she was killed?

17:51.080 --> 17:52.560
Yes.

17:55.240 --> 17:57.920
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

17:57.920 --> 18:01.400
♪ Remember me♪

18:01.400 --> 18:05.080
♪ 'Cause that's all you've got♪

18:05.080 --> 18:09.120
♪ 'Cause I'm a road♪

18:10.000 --> 18:12.520
[ Chuckles]
It is good stuff.

18:12.520 --> 18:14.840
GINA: The best.
So go easy, all right?

18:14.840 --> 18:16.680
Is that Gina Galvin with her?

18:16.680 --> 18:18.880
ELECTRA: Don't be funny.
I can handle it.

18:18.880 --> 18:20.600
[ Rapid chopping]

18:20.600 --> 18:22.000
What's that chopping sound?

18:22.000 --> 18:23.920
They're preparing drugs, Terry.

18:23.920 --> 18:26.040
Oh, right. Drugs.

18:26.040 --> 18:28.560
-Yeah, I thought so.
-[ Sneezes]

18:28.560 --> 18:30.880
GINA: That's going on your tab,
which, by the way,

18:30.880 --> 18:32.160
is well over its limit.

18:32.160 --> 18:33.840
ELECTRA: My tab?

18:33.840 --> 18:35.200
I just got you a spot
in the band.

18:35.200 --> 18:36.600
That's got to cover it.

18:36.600 --> 18:38.240
GINA: You haven't settled up
for months.

18:38.240 --> 18:40.280
We owe a lot of money.

18:40.280 --> 18:42.800
ELECTRA: You mean
you owe a lot of money.

18:46.960 --> 18:49.960
Had a small technical glitch.

18:49.960 --> 18:51.840
That's it, I'm afraid.

18:51.840 --> 18:52.920
[ Rock music plays ]

18:58.480 --> 19:01.320
[ Music continues,
cheers and applause ]

19:01.320 --> 19:05.440
NARRATOR: A stage-dive fail
of truly epic proportions

19:05.440 --> 19:07.680
had left Viv with back problems

19:07.680 --> 19:12.560
and a deep mistrust of
all East Lithuanian audiences.

19:12.560 --> 19:14.720
[ Cellphone rings ]

19:19.800 --> 19:21.360
[ Sighs ]

19:33.840 --> 19:36.680
[ Drone whirring ]

19:41.360 --> 19:44.160
So, do we arrest him
or caution him?

19:44.160 --> 19:46.160
Just need to have a few words
with her first.

19:46.160 --> 19:48.240
Any other instrument's
not a problem.

20:02.440 --> 20:04.720
-I'm the backbone of this band!
-TALLULAH: [ Gasps ]

20:05.680 --> 20:07.040
Stay away from me!

20:07.040 --> 20:08.880
You don't want to do this.

20:08.880 --> 20:11.640
Viv, put that thing down,
please.

20:11.640 --> 20:12.960
I'm sorry.

20:12.960 --> 20:15.360
Viv, I shouldn't
have gone along with it.

20:15.360 --> 20:18.960
We shouldn't have gone along
with any of it,

20:18.960 --> 20:21.560
but we can't change the past.

20:21.560 --> 20:24.080
I still have nightmares
about the lake.

20:25.800 --> 20:28.400
It was an accident, Tallulah.

20:29.320 --> 20:30.520
The brakes.

20:30.520 --> 20:31.720
I know.

20:31.720 --> 20:33.840
VIV:
Nikki was our friend.

20:33.840 --> 20:36.520
Why did we listen to them?

20:36.520 --> 20:38.760
TALLULAH: We were young.

20:38.760 --> 20:40.600
We were scared.

20:40.600 --> 20:42.560
[ Drone whirring ]

20:50.680 --> 20:51.520
[ Drone beeping ]

21:03.880 --> 21:05.840
[ Laughs ]

21:09.480 --> 21:11.400
[ Sighs ]

21:11.400 --> 21:14.480
Well,
there's the Wall of Rockbox.

21:14.480 --> 21:16.440
What was it you were after?

21:16.440 --> 21:20.560
A small ad for a documentary
filmmaker circa 2016.

21:20.560 --> 21:22.120
CARDOSA: Uh...

21:23.320 --> 21:25.480
-Shall we have a look?
-JANE: Mm-hmm.

21:33.880 --> 21:36.160
As the troubled drummer
faced the prospect

21:36.160 --> 21:38.440
of a lengthy incarceration,

21:38.440 --> 21:41.320
Matilda wondered
what it was in their past

21:41.320 --> 21:44.320
that they should not
have gone along with...

21:44.920 --> 21:48.480
...and how it related
to Nikki Holler.

21:58.120 --> 21:59.720
CAT: [ Sighs ]

22:02.760 --> 22:04.440
NIKKI: Cat?

22:05.120 --> 22:07.040
It's me -- Nikki.

22:08.800 --> 22:10.920
I'm about to get a ferry home.

22:11.880 --> 22:14.280
I wanted to say that...

22:14.280 --> 22:16.720
I missed you and I'm sorry.

22:17.320 --> 22:19.080
-[ Ship horn blows]
-ELECTRA: Come on, Nikki.

22:19.080 --> 22:21.480
Hurry up,
or we'll miss the boat.

22:23.760 --> 22:26.200
I really want to see you
and the baby,

22:26.200 --> 22:28.560
maybe give things
another shot...

22:28.560 --> 22:30.920
except, this time,
there'll be three of us.

22:31.920 --> 22:34.000
ELECTRA: Come on, Nikki!

22:39.320 --> 22:41.600
The tour's not been the same
without you, Cat.

22:43.000 --> 22:44.520
I spent my 27th alone

22:44.520 --> 22:47.880
in some crappy hotel room
in Dusseldorf.

22:47.880 --> 22:50.760
Look, I'll call you tomorrow
when I get back.

22:54.760 --> 22:56.080
I love you.

22:57.680 --> 22:58.960
I love you, too.

22:58.960 --> 23:01.280
[ Line clicks, beep ]

23:09.200 --> 23:11.080
[ Tape rewinding ]

23:15.520 --> 23:18.160
I spent my 27th alone
in some crappy hotel room in --

23:18.160 --> 23:19.880
[ Tape rewinding ]

23:23.560 --> 23:25.840
I spent my 27th alone --

23:26.560 --> 23:28.640
[ Indistinct conversation ]

23:35.560 --> 23:37.280
[ Door opens ]

23:37.280 --> 23:38.720
Coordinates
for Len Savage's house.

23:38.720 --> 23:40.240
MATILDA: Ah.

23:40.240 --> 23:42.560
1-6-1.

23:42.560 --> 23:44.760
8-0-3.

23:45.440 --> 23:47.760
The lake...

23:47.760 --> 23:50.160
that gives Viv nightmares.

23:51.280 --> 23:54.320
"Carry your sin
through a moonlit wood."

23:54.320 --> 23:55.840
Moonlit wood.

24:00.880 --> 24:03.320
[ Keyboard clacking ]

24:03.320 --> 24:04.600
TERRY: Moon phases?
What...

24:04.600 --> 24:06.160
MATILDA: Hang on.

24:07.880 --> 24:10.200
Why 31st of July, 1985?

24:10.200 --> 24:13.080
That's the night Nikki Holler
drowned in Len Savage's pool.

24:13.080 --> 24:15.040
[ Keyboard clacking ]

24:16.520 --> 24:18.040
TERRY: Whoa.

24:20.800 --> 24:24.840
Yesterday, when I asked you
about an accident, you panicked.

24:24.840 --> 24:26.080
Why?

24:33.840 --> 24:35.320
Len's house.

24:35.320 --> 24:36.560
The lake.

24:36.560 --> 24:38.200
The woods.

24:38.200 --> 24:41.200
"Carry your sin
through a moonlit wood."

24:42.440 --> 24:44.920
Nikki was your friend.

24:44.920 --> 24:47.320
It's time the truth came out.

24:59.600 --> 25:01.440
We were nearly at Len's house.

25:04.800 --> 25:07.080
-ELECTRA: You got a beer?
-NIKKI: No, no.

25:07.080 --> 25:08.760
TALLULAH: Yo, Viv!

25:08.760 --> 25:10.920
ELECTRA: Len. Yeah.
Beer!

25:10.920 --> 25:12.920
-Here.
-ELECTRA: Thanks.

25:16.480 --> 25:19.440
VIV: I only took my eyes
off the road for a minute.

25:19.440 --> 25:21.080
-[ Water splashing ]
-Viv!

25:21.080 --> 25:23.360
Viv, wait! Aah!

25:23.360 --> 25:24.840
Aah!

25:27.600 --> 25:29.160
ELECTRA: Aah!

25:31.280 --> 25:33.200
The van was sinking.

25:35.760 --> 25:38.000
Nikki didn't make it out.

25:42.680 --> 25:43.880
[ Woman coughing ]

25:46.080 --> 25:48.920
Len reckoned
that we'd all end up in prison

25:48.920 --> 25:50.240
because of all the drugs
in the van.

25:50.240 --> 25:52.240
No, no!
I'm not doing that!

25:52.240 --> 25:56.200
Me and Tallulah didn't want to,
but Len and Susan made us.

25:56.200 --> 25:57.880
-Come on.
-LEN: It's what we have to do.

26:04.400 --> 26:07.880
VIV: Len said that we owed it
to the memory of Nikki

26:07.880 --> 26:10.080
to protect the band.

26:10.080 --> 26:11.880
We moved the body.

26:12.920 --> 26:15.560
MATILDA: Protect the band?
What for?

26:15.560 --> 26:18.600
VIV: Because nothing
was gonna stand in the way

26:18.600 --> 26:21.080
of making Susan a star.

26:21.720 --> 26:23.640
MATILDA: So the four of you
made it look like,

26:23.640 --> 26:27.800
after taking too many drugs,
Nikki drowned in the pool.

26:28.880 --> 26:31.560
A classic rock-n-roll death.

26:37.960 --> 26:43.520
And then, 33 years later,
Electra Bliss has the nerve

26:43.520 --> 26:46.520
to kick you out of the band...

26:46.520 --> 26:50.840
after you'd lived with the guilt
and the pain all that time.

26:50.840 --> 26:52.480
So you killed her.

26:52.480 --> 26:55.720
Look,
I'm a pill-popping alcoholic,

26:55.720 --> 26:58.040
my head's all messed up,

26:58.040 --> 26:59.960
and I've made
some terrible mistakes,

26:59.960 --> 27:04.560
but I swear to God --
I did not kill Susan or Len.

27:05.800 --> 27:07.520
-[ Knock on door, door opens ]
-TERRY: Matilda.

27:07.520 --> 27:08.960
Can I have a word?

27:08.960 --> 27:11.080
This interview is suspended.

27:17.800 --> 27:19.080
What is it, Terry?

27:19.080 --> 27:20.960
Uniform just called
from the house.

27:20.960 --> 27:22.360
They've searched
Gina Galvin's room.

27:22.360 --> 27:23.880
Did they find her stash
of cocaine?

27:23.880 --> 27:26.560
No, but Susan Foyle's
missing jacket

27:26.560 --> 27:28.080
was hidden in her suitcase.

27:28.080 --> 27:31.360
It must be worth a lot
of money, so the question is,

27:31.360 --> 27:34.080
did Gina kill her
for the Joplin jacket,

27:34.080 --> 27:37.560
or did she steal it when she'd
learned their singer was dead?

27:37.560 --> 27:40.120
And I still can't get through
to the record label.

27:40.120 --> 27:44.160
Also, your Aunt Cat's
waiting in reception.

27:44.160 --> 27:45.880
Says it's important.

27:52.040 --> 27:53.440
Have you heard of the 27 Club?

27:53.440 --> 27:55.200
Uh...yeah.

27:55.200 --> 27:57.160
The list of rock stars
who all died at that age.

27:57.160 --> 27:59.000
Janis Joplin was
a founding member.

27:59.000 --> 28:01.000
The jacket.

28:01.000 --> 28:04.120
Nikki drowned three weeks
after her 27th birthday.

28:04.120 --> 28:05.560
MATILDA:
Making her a member of the club.

28:05.560 --> 28:07.960
Exactly.
It's why Volcanic Youth

28:07.960 --> 28:10.280
named their next album
"Twenty Seven."

28:10.280 --> 28:12.120
I think it's all connected.

28:16.720 --> 28:20.920
There's [Sighs]
something I need to tell you.

28:22.000 --> 28:24.320
It's about Nikki.

28:34.240 --> 28:36.680
-BETH: Got it.
-JANE: Oh.

28:37.280 --> 28:39.040
Oh, hang on a minute.

28:39.040 --> 28:40.760
Fairsight Films.

28:40.760 --> 28:43.120
Rings a bell.

28:43.120 --> 28:45.440
They contacted me a couple
of years ago to ask

28:45.440 --> 28:47.840
if I'd got any archive footage
of Volcanic Youth.

28:47.840 --> 28:50.560
-And do you have any?
-Yes.

28:50.560 --> 28:51.840
A lot.

28:51.840 --> 28:53.040
Let's give them a ring.

28:54.720 --> 28:56.800
[ Ringing, beep ]

28:56.800 --> 28:59.120
TYNE: You have reached
the office of Steven W. Tyne

28:59.120 --> 29:00.880
at Retrodisc Records.

29:00.880 --> 29:02.760
Please leave a message.

29:02.760 --> 29:04.400
Strange.

29:04.400 --> 29:06.040
-It's now a record company.
-CARDOSA: Oh.

29:06.040 --> 29:08.440
Didn't Cat say
that's who Volcanic Youth

29:08.440 --> 29:09.800
have recently signed with?

29:09.800 --> 29:11.480
BETH: Yes.

29:18.680 --> 29:20.440
Here.

29:23.640 --> 29:26.440
I can't believe
they did that to her.

29:26.440 --> 29:29.560
I think Viv and Tallulah
were pressured into it.

29:29.560 --> 29:32.320
[ Scoffs ] Yeah, well,
Len always was a bully.

29:32.920 --> 29:35.680
I watched Electra Bliss
become one.

29:36.520 --> 29:38.120
Still...

29:38.880 --> 29:40.800
[ Sighs ]

29:42.800 --> 29:43.760
What is all that?

29:45.480 --> 29:47.520
Oh, it's a transcript
of the audio

29:47.520 --> 29:49.080
that was recording in the studio

29:49.080 --> 29:51.040
just before
Electra Bliss was murdered.

29:51.040 --> 29:53.280
-What, Susan said all this?
-MATILDA: Yeah.

29:53.280 --> 29:55.360
Though the last word
was hard to hear.

29:55.360 --> 29:56.920
The tape was slowing to a halt
as it was said.

29:56.920 --> 29:58.200
Well, I'll tell you right now,

29:58.200 --> 30:00.320
-it's not "sorry."
-How do you know?

30:00.320 --> 30:02.240
Because Susie never said "sorry"
in her life.

30:02.240 --> 30:04.480
Not to anyone.
Not once.

30:05.080 --> 30:07.360
Can you work a studio console?

30:07.360 --> 30:09.920
Yeah.
I know my way around one.

30:11.840 --> 30:13.760
[ Cellphone rings ]

30:15.440 --> 30:18.120
Beth?
Yeah, I'm with the kid now.

30:18.120 --> 30:20.640
We've think it's got something
to do with the 27 Club.

30:20.640 --> 30:21.960
BETH: The 27 Club?

30:21.960 --> 30:23.600
CAT: I'll put you on speaker.
Hang on.

30:23.600 --> 30:26.520
Mattie, we did some digging
into Fairsight Films

30:26.520 --> 30:29.280
and found they're now
called Retrodisc Records.

30:29.280 --> 30:31.000
MATILDA:
Volcanic Youth's record label.

30:31.000 --> 30:35.320
Yeah. Turns out Retrodisc
has never released any music.

30:35.320 --> 30:36.760
Well, maybe they're just
a new company.

30:36.760 --> 30:39.240
Well, that's what we thought,
but Patrick Cardosa

30:39.240 --> 30:41.040
rang 'round a few people,

30:41.040 --> 30:44.080
and none of them
have heard of Retrodisc

30:44.080 --> 30:47.280
or Fairsight Films
or Steven Tyne.

30:47.280 --> 30:49.440
MATILDA: We haven't been able
to contact him.

30:50.640 --> 30:55.480
Steven W. Tyne is not a man.

30:55.480 --> 30:58.840
He is an anagram.

30:59.520 --> 31:00.520
Twenty-seven.

31:00.520 --> 31:01.760
Oh, Mattie.

31:01.760 --> 31:03.280
I wanted to say it.

31:08.240 --> 31:10.360
-Keep everyone in the house.
-Yes.

31:24.680 --> 31:28.080
Well, this is the archive
footage that I have of them --

31:28.080 --> 31:31.040
concert clips and interviews.

31:31.040 --> 31:33.680
Right.
Well, where should we start?

31:34.320 --> 31:38.640
Well, there's a very rare copy
of an interview

31:38.640 --> 31:41.280
that Nikki Holler did
five weeks before she died.

31:41.280 --> 31:42.880
It was never broadcast.

31:42.880 --> 31:44.680
Out of a mark of respect
for her family.

31:44.680 --> 31:47.360
[ Blows ]

31:47.360 --> 31:50.920
In fact, Fairsight Films
wanted a copy of it.

31:52.240 --> 31:53.480
Ready?

32:11.040 --> 32:12.880
MAN: Volcanic Youth
have been threatening

32:12.880 --> 32:14.720
to break into the mainstream.

32:14.720 --> 32:16.840
Are you an ambitious band?

32:16.840 --> 32:17.840
[ Chuckles]

32:17.840 --> 32:20.480
[ Breathes deeply]

32:22.440 --> 32:27.440
I just play songs and hope
that some people like them.

32:27.440 --> 32:29.760
I don't really care
how many people.

32:29.760 --> 32:34.000
As long as I make a connection,
the numbers don't matter.

32:34.880 --> 32:35.760
ELECTRA:
[ Speaks indistinctly]

32:40.840 --> 32:41.960
[ Speaks indistinctly]

32:41.960 --> 32:43.960
So, what do you think?

32:43.960 --> 32:45.760
CAT: [ Sighs ]

32:46.400 --> 32:48.720
It does sound like "sorry."

32:48.720 --> 32:51.040
I just can't picture her
saying it.

32:53.720 --> 32:55.080
You want to know
about my mother.

32:56.520 --> 32:59.000
Well, she was
a pretty tough lady.

32:59.000 --> 33:02.080
I mean, she had to be.

33:02.080 --> 33:04.080
She brought me up on her own.

33:04.080 --> 33:06.080
MAN:
What about your father?

33:08.960 --> 33:11.000
I don't know who he was.

33:12.840 --> 33:15.680
My mum, she only told me
one thing about him.

33:20.520 --> 33:22.560
[ Cellphone rings ]

33:22.560 --> 33:24.840
Hm. Ah.

33:25.600 --> 33:27.200
Aunt Beth?

33:29.080 --> 33:31.400
Nikki Holler's dad
was in a band?

33:33.000 --> 33:34.400
Hang on.
Play it again, Cat.

33:37.240 --> 33:38.560
ELECTRA:
[ Speaks indistinctly]

33:40.920 --> 33:42.360
I know what Electra Bliss
is saying.

33:42.360 --> 33:45.000
It's not "sorry."
It's "Sir Ray."

33:45.000 --> 33:48.240
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

33:49.840 --> 33:51.240
Wait for me in the car.

33:51.240 --> 33:52.680
CAT: Okay, kid, but be careful.

33:52.680 --> 33:54.400
MATILDA: Yeah.

33:54.400 --> 33:55.680
CAT: [ Grunting ]

33:55.680 --> 33:57.840
SIR RAY:
Quiet, or I'll kill you.

34:01.720 --> 34:02.760
Where's Sir Ray?

34:02.760 --> 34:04.000
He's just gone to the bathroom.

34:04.000 --> 34:06.440
No one else leaves
for any reason.

34:07.280 --> 34:08.520
[ Gasping ]

34:11.120 --> 34:13.600
Tallulah?
Tallulah!

34:13.600 --> 34:15.280
She's been poisoned!

34:15.280 --> 34:16.679
-Hold her head. Hold it.
-Just keep her steady.

34:16.679 --> 34:18.719
-Keep her steady.
-TERRY: We're here.

34:18.719 --> 34:19.960
-Yeah, we're here.
-[ Tallulah screams ]

34:19.960 --> 34:22.199
We need an ambulance -- fast.

34:22.199 --> 34:23.320
KURT: Right here.

34:23.320 --> 34:25.440
OFFICER:
P.C. Foster, come in.

34:25.440 --> 34:26.639
Go ahead.

34:26.639 --> 34:28.800
OFFICER:
We have a situation at the gate.

34:30.360 --> 34:32.040
TERRY: D.S. Stone is en route.
Over.

34:32.040 --> 34:33.440
-Aah! [ Vomits ]
-KURT: We're here.

34:35.800 --> 34:38.199
[ Engine revs ]

34:38.199 --> 34:40.480
CAT: [ Grunts ]

34:40.480 --> 34:42.159
Get back.

34:42.159 --> 34:43.719
[ Engine revs ]

34:43.719 --> 34:46.880
Tell the officer
to let us leave.

34:46.880 --> 34:48.960
This won't bring Nikki back.

34:48.960 --> 34:51.199
They had to be held accountable.

34:51.199 --> 34:52.800
CAT:
That's what the courts are for.

34:52.800 --> 34:54.760
SIR RAY:
It was too long ago!

34:54.760 --> 34:59.640
Unless one of them confessed,
the evidence is all long gone.

34:59.640 --> 35:02.240
This was the only way.

35:05.560 --> 35:06.760
ELECTRA: Sir Ray.

35:06.760 --> 35:08.480
It's Len. Savage.

35:14.040 --> 35:15.200
Thanks.

35:15.840 --> 35:18.320
I won't let you take my aunt.

35:18.920 --> 35:21.280
I have no grievance with her.

35:21.280 --> 35:23.000
Why should I believe you?

35:23.000 --> 35:27.280
She didn't exploit my daughter's
death like the others.

35:27.280 --> 35:31.520
They moved her body
to save their asses

35:31.520 --> 35:36.080
and then used her death
to get headlines, to get famous.

35:36.080 --> 35:39.920
Huh! They even made
a bloody album about it!

35:39.920 --> 35:41.960
-"Twenty Seven."
-Yeah!

35:41.960 --> 35:43.880
But you're the mastermind,
aren't you?

35:43.880 --> 35:45.760
Hiring Jonas
to interview the band

35:45.760 --> 35:47.800
so you could decide
who was guilty,

35:47.800 --> 35:50.560
creating Retrodisc Records
to get them here,

35:50.560 --> 35:52.520
killing two of them,
maybe even three,

35:52.520 --> 35:54.400
judging by the state
Tallulah's in.

35:54.400 --> 35:57.600
She's a clever girl, your niece.

35:57.600 --> 35:59.080
[ Laughs ]

35:59.080 --> 36:02.280
You should be thanking me.

36:02.280 --> 36:04.520
It was all for Nikki.

36:04.520 --> 36:05.960
If you really cared about Nikki,

36:05.960 --> 36:08.040
you would have made contact
with her.

36:08.040 --> 36:09.520
I mean, you knew about her.

36:10.680 --> 36:12.400
Didn't you?

36:15.280 --> 36:17.640
WOMAN: "57 years ago,

36:17.640 --> 36:22.160
you chose not to be a parent
to the most amazing person.

36:22.160 --> 36:24.600
She called herself Nikki Holler,

36:24.600 --> 36:29.480
and she burned twice as bright
and half as long as most.

36:29.480 --> 36:32.320
Nikki's death
has never made sense to me,

36:32.320 --> 36:35.160
and I've spent many years
trying to find out

36:35.160 --> 36:37.840
what really happened
to our daughter.

36:37.840 --> 36:40.040
But now I'm out of time,

36:40.040 --> 36:42.000
-so it's your turn, Ray."
-[ Sobs ]

36:42.000 --> 36:44.120
WOMAN:
"Do not fail us again."

36:45.120 --> 36:48.680
I gave Nikki my talent.

36:48.680 --> 36:50.320
MATILDA:
You think that's enough?

36:50.320 --> 36:52.600
It's not.
It's nowhere near.

36:52.600 --> 36:54.200
What do you know about it?

36:54.200 --> 36:56.720
I know how it feels to have
an absent father,

36:56.720 --> 36:59.120
to wonder who he is and why
he's never been in contact.

36:59.120 --> 37:00.880
I know all about it.

37:02.600 --> 37:03.920
[ Engine revs ]

37:03.920 --> 37:06.080
Now get out of my way!

37:06.600 --> 37:07.840
Move it!

37:07.840 --> 37:12.280
Open the gates,
or this gets ugly!

37:12.280 --> 37:14.400
Do as he says, kid.

37:17.240 --> 37:19.520
-OFFICER: Move aside!
-OFFICER #2: Get back!

37:48.200 --> 37:49.920
How did you find out
what really happened?

37:49.920 --> 37:52.800
The backmasking.

37:52.800 --> 37:55.840
[ Rock music plays,
Electra singing indistinctly]

37:59.640 --> 38:04.920
ELECTRA: ♪ Carry your sin
through a moonlit wood♪

38:04.920 --> 38:07.000
It felt like a confession.

38:07.000 --> 38:09.440
MAN:
Now tell me about Nikki.

38:09.440 --> 38:12.600
I saw it in their eyes
when they talked about Nikki.

38:13.960 --> 38:16.200
-Their guilt.
-ELECTRA: When she died,

38:16.200 --> 38:17.800
I took the band
in a different direction,

38:17.800 --> 38:21.600
and that's when we actually
started having some success.

38:24.640 --> 38:27.240
And there was
Viv Collins' autobiography

38:27.240 --> 38:30.120
that was dedicated
to her therapist.

38:32.160 --> 38:35.000
You'd be surprised how 50 grand

38:35.000 --> 38:37.320
will persuade
a Harley Street shrink

38:37.320 --> 38:42.400
to spill their client's deepest,
darkest secrets.

38:45.520 --> 38:47.640
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

38:50.480 --> 38:51.640
[ Gasps ]

39:04.040 --> 39:05.680
You know, all these years,
I've blamed myself

39:05.680 --> 39:07.440
for not being there.

39:08.040 --> 39:09.880
I thought Nikki died
because she'd taken something

39:09.880 --> 39:12.080
or there was something

39:12.080 --> 39:14.160
I could have done to prevent it,
but...

39:17.680 --> 39:20.560
I may not have known Nikki
in life.

39:21.600 --> 39:24.120
But we'll meet each other soon.

39:26.080 --> 39:27.440
Well, I'll tell you one thing
about her.

39:29.040 --> 39:31.600
Nikki was nothing like you.

39:32.200 --> 39:33.600
And she would have hated
what you've done.

39:35.040 --> 39:36.160
-[ Engine revs ]
-[ Grunts ]

39:39.400 --> 39:40.560
Hey!

39:48.440 --> 39:49.640
Aunt Cat?

39:49.640 --> 39:51.120
[ Groans ]

39:51.120 --> 39:53.600
Oh, I'm getting too old
for this.

39:56.080 --> 39:58.960
He said he wanted to be
with Nikki.

40:00.280 --> 40:03.440
I think I know
which way he was going.

40:03.440 --> 40:04.600
Come on.

40:16.440 --> 40:18.080
We're too late.

40:20.320 --> 40:23.000
-What are you doing?
-We can't let him win.

41:12.360 --> 41:13.960
[ Vehicle door opens ]

41:34.040 --> 41:36.160
-[ Police radio chatter ]
-See you at the station.

41:36.160 --> 41:37.680
OFFICER: Ma'am.

41:39.200 --> 41:40.800
I spoke to the hospital.

41:40.800 --> 41:42.160
Tallulah's gonna be okay.

41:42.160 --> 41:43.360
Luckily,
she didn't drink it all.

41:43.360 --> 41:45.640
She'd be dead
if she'd finished the glass.

41:49.840 --> 41:51.160
You know, you did
the right thing, kid.

41:53.760 --> 41:56.520
-Are you coming?
-Uh...

41:56.520 --> 41:58.240
I'm gonna stay here awhile.

41:59.600 --> 42:02.400
-Mattie.
-Hmm?

42:02.400 --> 42:03.600
What you said about your dad...

42:03.600 --> 42:05.200
Oh, forget it.

42:05.200 --> 42:07.960
I was just trying to get him
to connect.

42:07.960 --> 42:10.240
I had you three.
It's...

42:10.240 --> 42:12.320
It's been more than enough.

42:18.840 --> 42:23.560
NARRATOR: It had been 22 years,
17 days, and 12 hours

42:23.560 --> 42:27.480
since Matilda decided
never to ask about her father,

42:27.480 --> 42:28.920
and she suddenly wondered

42:28.920 --> 42:32.160
if she needed to re-evaluate
her thinking.

42:35.720 --> 42:38.840
Meanwhile, Cat's mind turned
to the other great sadness

42:38.840 --> 42:40.840
she still carried --

42:40.840 --> 42:44.680
the relationship
with her only child, Annie,

42:44.680 --> 42:46.000
or lack thereof.

42:46.000 --> 42:48.280
[ Ringing ]

42:48.280 --> 42:50.200
ANNIE: Hello.
This is Annie Stone.

42:50.200 --> 42:51.880
I'm sorry I can't take
your call at the minute,

42:51.880 --> 42:54.160
but leave a message,
and I'll get back to you.

42:56.560 --> 42:57.920
[ Sighs ]

43:15.600 --> 43:17.960
Quite the sweep
from Sergeant Stone.

43:17.960 --> 43:20.200
Good work.
Both of you.

43:20.200 --> 43:21.680
Thank you, sir.

43:26.040 --> 43:28.800
It's a pretty dramatic end
to your film.

43:28.800 --> 43:31.560
Should you need an interview,
one could be easily arranged.

43:31.560 --> 43:34.080
[ Engine starts ]

43:34.080 --> 43:37.400
That would have been great,
but now I know the truth,

43:37.400 --> 43:39.600
I'm not sure I want
any more part of it.

43:51.640 --> 43:54.000
JANE:
I really think she'll like him.

43:54.000 --> 43:56.160
How did you manage
to convince her this time?

43:56.160 --> 43:59.040
She's under the impression that
this is just a family outing.

43:59.040 --> 44:00.920
-CAT: Mm.
-The words "blind" and "date"

44:00.920 --> 44:02.760
were not mentioned.

44:03.960 --> 44:05.920
NARRATOR: Concerned to see
they were one short

44:05.920 --> 44:07.440
for their skittles team,

44:07.440 --> 44:10.000
Matilda was excited to spot
a potential recruit.

44:10.000 --> 44:11.960
Daniel. Hi.

44:11.960 --> 44:14.960
-Hey.
-Oh. Hi, Melinda.

44:14.960 --> 44:16.800
[ Chuckles ]
Come on.

44:18.720 --> 44:20.920
Looks like we're teammates.

44:20.920 --> 44:23.880
Matilda immediately suspected
this coincidence

44:23.880 --> 44:25.680
to be one of her aunts' making.

44:25.680 --> 44:27.640
-I want that hamper.
-Yeah.

44:27.640 --> 44:30.400
Not one to let a setback
dampen her spirits,

44:30.400 --> 44:33.120
Matilda determined that the
best way to enjoy the evening

44:33.120 --> 44:37.080
was to win -- and win big.

44:39.000 --> 44:41.000
For any victory,
however trivial,

44:41.000 --> 44:42.440
would bring with it a respite

44:42.440 --> 44:45.520
from her unresolved feelings
for Daniel

44:45.520 --> 44:50.200
and the recently resurfaced
questions of who her father was

44:50.200 --> 44:52.880
and whether he was
still out there somewhere,

44:52.880 --> 44:55.000
waiting to be found.

44:56.120 --> 45:00.520
♪ Keep things a mystery ♪

45:01.480 --> 45:06.560
♪ You know they have history ♪

45:09.240 --> 45:14.440
♪ And, no, it never ends well ♪

45:14.440 --> 45:18.920
♪ It's called death by vinyl ♪♪

45:19.680 --> 45:22.480
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]
